Sony’s Obsolete Software Exposed Network to Attack, Report Says

-- B y   P a v e l   A l p e y e v
-- 
2011-05-18T03:17:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/sony-s-obsolete-software-exposed-network-to-attack-report-says.html
Sony Corp. (6758) ’s use of outdated network
software on its PlayStation Network and Qriocity entertainment
services has helped hackers steal data on more than 100 million
users, according to  Computer Bild .  The company used software that was outdated for as long as
five years, the report by the online technology publication
said, citing server scan logs provided by hacker collective
Anonymous. Sony used the OpenSSH 4.4 data-encryption software,
while the most recent version is 5.7, it said.  Sony was also running the 2.2.10 version of Apache server
software, the report said. The most recent iteration of the
program is 2.2.18, according to its  website .  Mai Hora, a Tokyo-based spokeswoman at Sony’s games unit,
declined to comment on the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pavel Alpeyev in Tokyo at 
 palpeyev@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
